1
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:35,840
Three.

2
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,479
Ignition.

3
00:01:41,479 --> 00:01:42,080
Liftoff.

4
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:49,650
Exploring the universe is humanity's oldest dream.

5
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:52,620
If satellites are the cattle and sheep we graze,

6
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:55,280
then the universe is our pasture.

7
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,560
I'm Wu Wei,

8
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:05,850
a star grazer at the China Aerospace Flight Control Center.

9
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,600
This is our story.

10
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,800
The competition is about to begin.

11
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,730
Please enter in an orderly manner with your tickets.

12
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,520
Wake up.

13
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,600
The competition is starting soon.

14
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,360
Come take a look.

15
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,820
The machine stopped spinning again. Hurry.

16
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,160
Look.

17
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,250
The dog's wheel won't spin.

18
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,560
The drive system keeps reporting errors.

19
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,960
Bro, think of something.

20
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,079
Think of something.

21
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:30,480
Wei,

22
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:30,920
think of a way.

23
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,560
Don't you want to impress the flight control leaders?

24
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,680
That's Qin Bojun.

25
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,880
Qin Bojun!

26
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:37,340
Your interview success depends on this.

27
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,400
Flight control.

28
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,680
He might really be my interviewer.

29
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,079
Then hurry up, bro.

30
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:45,560
The competition is starting soon.

31
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:48,040
If we take home a 3rd consecutive championship,

32
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,400
your interview will be a breeze.

33
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,400
A breeze.

34
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,320
Let me eat a bite first.

35
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,200
Let me think.

36
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,600
Take out the spare part.

37
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,800
Why is there another robot here?

38
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,400
Whose is this? Which team?

39
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,440
Doesn't matter which team.

40
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,360
Must be rich kids.

41
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,880
Looks like they spent a lot.

42
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:12,640
Rich or not,

43
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:14,360
they're just here for the ride, you know?

44
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,290
Buying such good parts is useless.

45
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,040
We are definitely first.

46
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:18,760
Let me see.

47
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,280
It has so many random modules.

48
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,360
So flashy.

49
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,800
Just a vase, is it useful?

50
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,840
Pay-to-win players. I hate this kind the most.

51
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,500
Who are you? Don't touch that.

52
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,690
He pushed me.

53
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,320
Who are you?

54
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,520
This is our Polytech Team lounge.

55
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,920
This is our Hangda lounge.

56
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,320
Did you see the big letters on the door?

57
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:43,780
Wrong room. Sorry.

58
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,360
So awkward.

59
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,760
Let's go.

60
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:56,400
Go.

61
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,079
Wait.

62
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,079
It suddenly won't turn on.

63
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:00,080
What did you just touch?

64
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:00,840
Did you touch it?

65
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,360
No.

66
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:01,960
He didn't touch it.

67
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,760
Did you?

68
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:03,200
No.

69
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,260
He didn't touch it, and neither did I.

70
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,520
Impossible.

71
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,120
I just checked it before leaving.

72
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,520
Why is it suddenly reporting an error?

73
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:12,000
You don't like being called a vase,

74
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,560
but you don't even understand your own stuff.

75
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,560
And you ask me?

76
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,320
Stop playing dumb.

77
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,399
It means you are setting us up.

78
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,760
Forget it. Let them go.

79
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,079
Look.

80
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,640
Your teammate knows what it means.

81
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:24,080
Take your scrap metal and get out.

82
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,480
Who are you calling scrap metal?

83
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,280
Not necessary.

84
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,720
They can't mess with my stuff.

85
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:37,020
You wouldn't understand.

86
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,080
Who cares what it means.

87
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,159
Let's go.

88
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,409
Pay-to-win player. Trash.

89
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,050
What did you say?

90
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,320
Just go.

91
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:51,080
So stupid.

92
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,120
So stupid.

93
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:54,640
I should have talked back to them.

94
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,800
What wouldn't we understand?

95
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,880
Who didn't understand?

96
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,000
Your parts are just a little more expensive.

97
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,330
Who didn't understand?

98
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,880
A hero's origin doesn't matter.

99
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,940
He's the one who doesn't understand.

100
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,280
What does he mean exactly?

101
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,000
Wei.

102
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,440
Wei, calm down.

103
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,480
So energetic.

104
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,840
Calm down.

105
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,960
It's too late to react now.

106
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:18,760
We lost the argument, but we'll win on the field.

107
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:20,240
Brother, check where the robot is broken.

108
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,040
I checked.

109
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,720
Ours is a brushed motor.

110
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,650
It short-circuited and burnt out.

111
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,120
I told you to get the spare one.

112
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:26,980
I didn't buy it.

113
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,520
Brother.

114
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,880
We only have a little fund left.

115
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,680
We bought self-heating hot pot with all of it.

116
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,800
And I didn't even get a bite.

117
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:33,840
You two ate it all.

118
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,800
You shouldn't eat it either.

119
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:46,040
No problem.

120
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:49,200
Was the joystick not connected just now?

121
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,480
You scared me.

122
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,940
I thought they really messed with it.

123
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,920
When will you give me the prize money?

124
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:58,120
The match hasn't started. What prize money?

125
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,080
Let's win first.

126
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,970
We will definitely win.

127
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:01,680
Try it.

128
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,720
Is there any problem?

129
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:04,680
No problem.

130
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,860
I rented an apartment.

131
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,000
If I don't pay the rent today,

132
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,400
they won't keep it for me.

133
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,520
I think

134
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,240
even if we win the game and get the prize money,

135
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,280
you probably won't be able to rent that apartment.

136
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,880
Are you really not going to pursue a Ph.D.?

137
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,800
It's an exemption from the exam, bro.

138
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,130
It's a pity to give it up.

139
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:22,800
I'm tired of studying.

140
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,400
You haven't discussed it with your family, have you?

141
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,120
Mrs. Chen Bing will hit the roof if she knows.

142
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,160
Just leave it.

143
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,240
Okay, this is it.

144
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,680
Pick a good one from the rotten ones.

145
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,890
Find me a zip tie.

146
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,440
The size of this old-fashioned gasket is wrong.

147
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,570
It needs to be fixed.

148
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,960
Zip tie.

149
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,930
Brother, we only have this.

150
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,720
Okay, there are rough ways to play.

151
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,400
I have to make something out of it today.

152
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,680
Let Qin Bojun see.

153
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,920
Then it will be easy to get into Flight Control.

154
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:29,840
Son.

155
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,160
Where are you?

156
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:34,220
Your dad and I have arrived at the school.

157
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,320
Dad.

158
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,200
Did you tell my mom or not?

159
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,159
My son is the most handsome.

160
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:45,920
Ying Ziqi.

161
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:49,800
No.

162
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,600
I did.

163
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,480
But you might need to tell her again yourself.

164
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,560
What are you doing?

165
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,960
Ziqi's speech is coming up soon.

166
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:04,560
Hurry up.

167
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,280
Mrs. Chen.

168
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,720
Why don't you go ahead?

169
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,120
I need to go to the restroom.

170
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,360
You're always stalling.

171
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,420
Hurry up. Let's go.

172
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,360
Mr. Qiao.

173
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,040
Hello, Mr. Qiao.

174
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,240
Mrs. Chen, what brings you here?

175
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,500
Of course I'd come to Ziqi's graduation.

176
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,200
Doesn't he have a speech?

177
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,880
Our Ziqi...

178
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,720
For all the major events in his life,

179
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,480
I have to be present.

180
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,040
You... you don't know?

181
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,000
Know what?

182
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,360
After Ying Ziqi finished his graduation procedures,

183
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,690
he already left school.

184
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,640
Left school?

185
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,520
Then where did he go?

186
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:37,240
He said he doesn't plan to pursue a Ph.D.

187
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,159
And his recommendation quota for postgraduate studies...

188
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:40,280
he gave that up too.

189
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:43,120
Mr. Ying knows all about this.

190
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:48,240
This...

191
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,500
What is he trying to do?

192
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,480
What are you doing?

193
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,360
Why didn't you tell me such a big thing?

194
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,160
Ziqi said he has his own ideas.

195
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:54,720
He...

196
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,280
Where is Ziqi now?

197
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,480
Call him! Call him now!

198
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,400
I'm calling.

199
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,520
Mrs. Chen!

200
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,320
My friends,

201
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,560
welcome to this year's

202
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:05,400
Aerospace Cup Robot Combat Competition!

203
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,320
Today we will have our final match.

204
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:11,320
The Hangda Team will face this competition's dark horse,

205
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,800
the Ligong Team.

206
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,640
Is your big baby fixed?

207
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,540
Yeah, we'll crush you in a bit.

208
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,360
Good parts are useless.

209
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,320
True heroes don't care about origins.

210
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,000
Scrap metal can still strike back.

211
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:24,840
Strike back?

212
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,280
You've read too many web novels.

213
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,730
See you in the arena.

214
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:29,240
All right.

215
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,300
Our exciting match is about to begin.

216
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,480
As everyone knows,

217
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,760
previous robot competitions

218
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,280
have provided national aerospace projects

219
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,120
with a large number of outstanding talents.

220
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,560
Today, we are even more honored to invite

221
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,480
the chief designer of the China Aerospace Flight Control Center,

222
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,640
Mr. Qin Bojun.

223
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,840
If the defending champion, the Hangda Team,

224
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,760
can win this competition today,

225
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,440
they will break the competition record

226
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:54,170
and become the first ever to win three consecutive championships.

227
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:57,640
All right.

228
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,640
First to appear is the born champion,

229
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,720
Jedi.

230
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,840
Weighing 13.6 kilograms,

231
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,640
and with a two-wheel drive.

232
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:05,640
It is equipped with a 20-millimeter-thick

233
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,840
aluminum alloy armor all around.

234
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:09,520
Its rotational speed can reach 12,000 RPM.

235
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,600
It is known as the strongest tank in history,

236
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,200
a drum spinner combat robot.

237
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,080
And entering next

238
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,520
is a combat robot that supports

239
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,040
both vertical and offset horizontal spinning modules,

240
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,080
Storm Dog.

241
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:25,120
The vertical and offset horizontal spinning modules

242
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,680
make Storm Dog's driving force, control,

243
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,880
and even grip

244
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,200
more precise.

245
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,340
A well-deserved strongest warrior.

246
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,080
It's worth mentioning that

247
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:34,920
the new generation of technologies

248
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,640
you see in this competition

249
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,040
will be applied in the future

250
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:41,040
to various fields including the aerospace industry.

251
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:46,440
Okay.

252
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,280
Our match

253
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:49,240
begins now.

254
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:56,680
Storm Dog launches the first round of attack

255
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:58,160
against Jedi.

256
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,760
Although Jedi managed to dodge it,

257
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,600
it still seems a bit flustered.

258
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,760
Storm Dog's large blunt blade

259
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:07,440
hit Jedi's armor.

260
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,250
What's the use of expensive parts?

261
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,200
Relax.

262
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,720
Jedi's armor

263
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,080
shows no fear despite the impact.

264
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,720
Jedi is hit hard again.

265
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,720
How will it respond?

266
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,080
It's just for show.

267
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:31,360
Storm Dog has always dominated the arena with strong attacks,

268
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,800
but Jedi happens to be a robot

269
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,440
that excels in defense.

270
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,000
This is destined to be

271
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,400
a wonderful duel between spear and shield.

272
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,280
It dodged!

273
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,520
Jedi actually dodged

274
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:43,120
Storm Dog's impact.

275
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,040
Why dodge?

276
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,400
Think of something, bro.

277
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,130
Don't you want the prize money?

278
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:49,180
Let me do it.

279
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,340
They swapped drivers.

280
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,080
Swapping won't help.

281
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,440
I'll teach him a lesson.

282
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,760
It's a brushed motor.

283
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,960
Jedi's brushed motor,

284
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,600
paired with the two-wheel drive system,

285
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,320
exerts the advantage of low speed and high torque,

286
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,320
dodging Storm Dog's savage impact.

287
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,880
Beautiful!

288
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,760
A thrust back!

289
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,480
What a pity. Storm Dog is bounced off.

290
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,800
Jedi is unstoppable. Amazing!

291
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:20,000
Jedi once again dodged

292
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,130
Storm Dog's attack.

293
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,080
Now Storm Dog

294
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,080
has been pursuing Jedi.

295
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:27,920
All right.

296
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,120
We see that Jedi has changed its tactics.

297
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,520
It uses its agility advantage

298
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,360
to keep avoiding

299
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,280
direct frontal conflict with Storm Dog.

300
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:36,560
Does Jedi have any

301
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,480
ultimate moves we don't know about?

302
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:40,520
What exactly is it brewing?

303
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,720
How will Storm Dog deal with Jedi?

304
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,920
What kind of surprise will it bring us?

305
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:47,600
Now.

306
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,890
Storm Doggo reveals its sword.

307
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,000
What happened? What happened?

308
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,120
Storm Doggo crashed into the wall!

309
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,960
Jedi Knight uses its advantage

310
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,480
to catch the enemy in a trap.

311
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,280
Right now,

312
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,340
Jedi Knight has activated its taunt.

313
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,120
It's stuck.

314
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,240
Storm Doggo's giant blunt sword

315
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,560
just took a hit,

316
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,560
and it's stuck.

317
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:11,400
Obviously, Jedi Knight

318
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,200
noticed Storm Doggo's problem.

319
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,560
Will Jedi Knight

320
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,800
be able to seize this opportunity?

321
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:19,320
The chance is here.

322
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,720
Jedi Knight is about to launch a fatal blow.

323
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,160
Storm Doggo, watch out!

324
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:23,690
Dodge it!

325
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:24,980
Wait a bit more.

326
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,160
Jedi Knight is making its move.

327
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,160
Jedi Knight is getting closer.

328
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,690
What should Storm Doggo do?

329
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:45,180
Storm Doggo completes a counterattack!

330
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,120
The most exciting moment of this robotics competition!

331
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,280
Storm Doggo uses its broken

332
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,560
blunt sword and regular sword

333
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,400
to cut through Jedi Knight.

334
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,640
Jedi Knight has completely lost its mobility.

335
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:59,200
Storm Doggo is the final champion!

336
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,160
Alright, let's take another look

337
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,880
at that thrilling moment just now.

338
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:09,320
We won.

339
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:09,880
Wei, we won.

340
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:10,600
Wei.

341
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,160
Storm Doggo was cornered

342
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,600
but didn't give up.

343
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,280
Instead, it used its dual weapon system

344
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,280
to target Jedi Knight.

345
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,960
Three-peat! Three-peat! Three-peat!

346
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:23,840
This is all thanks to Storm Doggo's operator,

347
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,720
the Aviation University team's rich experience,

348
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,320
and the power of Storm Doggo's weapon system.

349
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,280
Referee,

350
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:43,500
the opponent is overweight and broke the rules.

351
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:49,760
How is that possible?

352
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,160
When we registered and during the group stage,

353
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,160
it weighed 13.9 kilograms every time.

354
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,680
You must have weighed it wrong, referee.

355
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:55,680
Measure it again.

356
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,200
It's over 14 kilograms.

357
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,600
It's indeed a violation.

358
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:02,770
According to the rules, we can't declare you the winner.

359
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,720
Jedi Knight weighs 13.6 kilograms.

360
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,240
When the weapon module reaches full speed,

361
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,920
it generates 4,500 joules,

362
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:12,800
capable of withstanding

363
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,880
an attack from something 0.4 kilograms heavier than itself.

364
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,280
Unless Storm Doggo exceeds this weight...

365
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:18,760
Wei,

366
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,400
how can it be overweight?

367
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,860
We didn't touch anything.

368
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,040
Zip ties. Zip ties.

369
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:32,000
Ladies and gentlemen,

370
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,720
an unexpected situation just occurred.

371
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,160
The Aviation University team's robot, Storm Doggo,

372
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,640
exceeded the competition's weight limit.

373
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,480
After discussions between the on-site referees

374
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:42,360
and the competition committee,

375
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,880
the winner of this final is

376
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,260
the Polytechnic team!

377
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:52,220
I didn't see a counterattack,

378
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,360
but it's definitely a piece of junk.

379
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,600
I realized you're really asking for it.

380
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,260
Cut the crap. What did you say?

381
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,240
The referee is here.

382
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,080
Wei, don't.

383
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:00,880
One more time.

384
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,520
I can beat you even though I'm lighter than you. Do you believe it?

385
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,040
Come on,

386
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:03,640
both of you.

387
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:04,200
Come on.

388
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,960
I'm asking you. Why are you looking at your phone?

389
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:06,280
Let's do it again.

390
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,640
I don't have time to play with you.

391
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:08,160
Do it again.

392
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:08,480
Don't go.

393
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:08,840
I'm leaving.

394
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:09,640
Don't pull me.

395
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,000
Don't forget to take the prize money.

396
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:11,480
Wei.

397
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,010
Who's playing with you two?

398
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,360
Forget it.

399
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,160
Ying Ziqi.

400
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,440
Mr. Qin, long time no see.

401
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,440
You look stunning today.

402
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,280
I'm almost

403
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,040
blinded.

404
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,480
That's the Ying Ziqi I remember.

405
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,160
How come I heard that you

406
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,090
gave up the Ph.D. recommendation?

407
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:37,520
Yes.

408
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:41,120
Then you must have a better choice.

409
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,080
Not yet.

410
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:45,640
It's been almost a year since your internship ended.

411
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:46,640
What's your plan?

412
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:48,360
I...

413
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,160
I have no plan yet.

414
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,960
Mr. Qin, I have an emergency right now.

415
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,760
I have to...

416
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:00,480
Okay.

417
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,720
Go ahead.

418
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,460
Why are there no windows here?

419
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:29,840
What do you want to do?

420
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:30,840
What do I want?

421
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,680
You scammed me out of my third consecutive championship.

422
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,800
And you want to leave?

423
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,000
The match is over.

424
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,400
Go to the referee if you have complaints.

425
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,760
What's there to appeal?

426
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,080
You said it's over.

427
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,360
Where can I appeal?

428
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,760
You can't afford to lose, so you play by the rules?

429
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:43,160
Rules are rules.

430
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:45,100
I have no time to play with you.

431
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,460
Don't go anywhere.

432
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,040
If you have the guts, compete with me, Wu Wei,

433
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,240
for one more round.

434
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,370
Are you going or not?

435
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,080
Ziqi.

436
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:54,520
Driver.

437
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:56,040
Stop the car. Stop now.

438
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,290
Just tell me if you dare.

439
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:00,680
Ziqi.

440
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:01,920
Ziqi.

441
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,520
Ziqi, stop right there.

442
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,640
Ziqi, don't run.

443
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,800
Ying Ziqi, stop right there.

444
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:09,920
Mr. Chen.

445
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,400
Hurry, after him.

446
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:12,400
Slow down.

447
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,360
Hurry, catch him.

448
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:13,920
Okay.

449
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,680
Ying Ziqi.

450
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:18,120
Handsome.

451
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:20,320
I'm talking to you. Are you going or not?

452
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:22,240
You're the handsome one.

453
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:24,840
Bai.

454
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,740
You brought all the luggage over, right?

455
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,520
Okay.

456
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:31,760
What?

457
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,360
You told my mom?

458
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:55,040
Mom.

459
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:59,280
You've grown up, your wings are strong,

460
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:01,640
and you want to fly solo. Want to make your own decisions, right?

461
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,640
Such a big matter,

462
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:05,080
why didn't you discuss it with me?

463
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,480
You have a guaranteed Ph.D. spot but refuse to take it.

464
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,520
Are you letting me down?

465
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,080
Are you letting your advisor down?

466
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,000
Are you letting yourself down?

467
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:15,720
Mrs. Chen.

468
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,080
Are you trying to cover for him?

469
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:21,120
Acting like this,

470
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,120
you're going to ruin your son.

471
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,320
No, it's not that.

472
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:26,760
I need to use the restroom,

473
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:28,400
I really need to pee.

474
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,000
Go.

475
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:39,280
Son,

476
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:41,240
tell me,

477
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,680
what are you really thinking?

478
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:44,000
Give me a reason.

479
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:46,360
Speak.

480
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:50,000
Isn't it good to stay at the university as a professor after getting your Ph.D.?

481
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,320
Your grandparents,

482
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:54,360
even your disappointing dad,

483
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:55,880
are all Ph.D.s.

484
00:19:57,520 --> 00:20:00,600
I didn't have the conditions to continue studying back then,

485
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,160
but I didn't miss out on

486
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:04,000
my part-time master's and Ph.D. degrees.

487
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,080
I've been a teacher all my life,

488
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,400
and I can't even educate my own child properly.

489
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:10,480
Where do I put my face?

490
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,320
There's no room for discussion.

491
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,400
You must study it.

492
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,740
What are you doing?

493
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:22,780
I wasn't planning on discussing it with you.

494
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:24,440
Xiao... Xiaoqi! Xiaoqi!

495
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,320
Whatever it is,

496
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,760
go home and talk it over with your mom.

497
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,760
No, look at him!

498
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,120
Why are you stopping me?

499
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:30,480
Go stop him!

500
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:31,240
My bag!

501
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:31,840
Okay.

502
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,400
Slow down.

503
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,280
Xiaoqi, wait for me!

504
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,000
This kid...

505
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,760
Xiaoqi! Xiaoqi!

506
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,360
Xiaoqi!

507
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:44,160
Slow down.

508
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:45,600
Come here.

509
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,280
Xiaoqi, come here,

510
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,400
hurry and help out.

511
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,560
Hurry up.

512
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:51,960
Mrs. Chen, are you okay?

513
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:52,680
I can't.

514
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,880
Hurry up!

515
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,400
I can't. Mrs. Chen, come.

516
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,360
Slow down.

517
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:57,370
Quick, sit down.

518
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:58,720
Here, let me see.

519
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,130
How's your foot?

520
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,280
Does it hurt?

521
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,640
How could it not hurt?

522
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:07,800
Not only does my leg hurt,

523
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,000
my heart hurts too.

524
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,040
Xiaoqi,

525
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:17,440
Xiaoqi.

526
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,400
I'm so anxious,

527
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,920
isn't it all for your own good?

528
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,200
From childhood to adulthood,

529
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,760
how many cram schools did I accompany you to?

530
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,800
How many competitions did we attend,

531
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:30,400
rain or shine?

532
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:33,680
Parents love their children,

533
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:37,120
so they plan far ahead for them.

534
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:38,840
You know that, right?

535
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:40,240
Xiaoqi,

536
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:41,580
listen to your dad.

537
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,040
Let's talk about it when we get home.

538
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,880
Do you really want to make your mom mad?

539
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,480
Go home with Mom.

540
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,250
Give me the car keys.

541
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:56,860
Bring the car here.

542
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,100
Go quickly.

543
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,560
Let's go home.

544
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:04,320
All right.

545
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,690
Let's not be angry anymore.

546
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,300
Certificate of Honor.

547
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:30,440
The 12th National Math Olympiad.

548
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,840
The first place goes to

549
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:34,440
Chen Xiaoyi from Zhongda Primary School.

550
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,160
The second place goes to

551
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,880
Ying Ziqi from Hang Kong Primary School.

552
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,680
Wu Wei, what do you want to show me?

553
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,280
My mom is urging me to go home.

554
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:08,040
What's the rush?

555
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,640
Ying Ziqi,

556
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:11,970
hold this for me.

557
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,480
This is a rocket built by your big brother himself.

558
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:22,280
Isn't it cool?

559
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:24,400
I'll let you see today

560
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,560
what a rocket is.

561
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,800
Let me demonstrate it for you.

562
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,480
According to Newton's third law,

563
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:32,480
if you open a hole in a rocket filled with high-pressure gas,

564
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:33,520
the gas will shoot out,

565
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,000
generating thrust.

566
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,640
When the thrust is greater than the rocket's own gravity,

567
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,840
the rocket takes off.

568
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,640
Today, let your big brother tell you

569
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,400
what the sea of stars is

570
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,960
and what flying freely is.

571
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,040
Oh my god!

572
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:00,080
Who is it?

573
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:02,400
I'm out of here.

574
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,930
Don't say you saw me, got it?

575
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:05,360
Wait for me!

576
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:08,440
Wait for me!

577
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:09,720
Who?

578
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,560
What are you doing?

579
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:11,290
Who did this?

580
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,160
Tell me!

581
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:15,800
I know it wasn't you.

582
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,160
Was it

583
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,240
that boy Wu Wei?

584
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,000
Traitor!

585
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,760
Who did it?

586
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,450
Let's see where you can run!

587
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,080
I didn't expect

588
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:36,280
you to be a traitor with those thick eyebrows and big eyes.

589
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,280
I'll kill you!

590
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:42,760
Hit me! Hit me!

591
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,020
Invincible transformation!

592
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:52,720
Mom.

593
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:55,040
Who did you fight with this time?

594
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,180
I'm calling your teacher.

595
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:58,320
No, no, no.

596
00:24:59,400 --> 00:24:59,880
No.

597
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:00,800
No, Mom.

598
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,880
It was Ying Ziqi from my class.

599
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:05,240
We were just playing around.

600
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,440
Just a friendly spar.

601
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,300
Friendly spar?

602
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:08,360
Was it a friendly spar,

603
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:09,960
or did you provoke him first?

604
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,840
Did you break the glass of the bicycle shed downstairs?

605
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,400
You are getting more and more outrageous.

606
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:17,000
The glass thing was just an operational error.

607
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,160
Mom,

608
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:20,520
are you not feeling well again?

609
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:22,200
Don't be angry. Don't be angry, Mom.

610
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,060
I'll apologize to Grandpa Zhang.

611
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,640
Mom.

612
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:28,760
It's nothing.

613
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:30,850
I'm just a little tired.

614
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:33,280
Mom.

615
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:36,600
I was too naughty and playful.

616
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,120
I made you sick with anger.

617
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:39,960
How could that be?

618
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,200
Come and sit.

619
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:47,370
I'm not stopping you from playing.

620
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,760
I just don't want you to mess around.

621
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:51,840
If you like making things,

622
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,880
you should study it properly.

623
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,080
Whatever you do,

624
00:25:55,080 --> 00:25:56,940
don't just do it half-heartedly.

625
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:59,180
Both studying and playing

626
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,120
require your full attention.

627
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:02,370
Understood?

628
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,080
By the way, Mom.

629
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:09,080
There's a rocket competition at the Youth Palace hobby class.

630
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:11,680
I heard the winner gets to attend a summer camp.

631
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:14,170
I will definitely study it well this time.

632
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,480
I'll surely bring back the championship.

633
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:17,760
I'll give it to you then.

634
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:19,360
You have to compete well.

635
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,720
If you have the guts, compete with me, Wu Wei,

636
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,520
once again.

637
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:30,880
Then tell Mom,

638
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:32,640
what is this about?

639
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:36,920
Didn't we agree

640
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:38,560
to throw it away?

641
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:40,160
Why are you still keeping it?

642
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:45,880
Xiaoba.

643
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,880
You're on your own from now on.

644
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:51,440
Don't!

645
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,000
Are you crazy?

646
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,610
Don't you know turtles hibernate?

647
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,120
It's almost frozen into turtle jelly.

648
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,380
How can you be so cruel?

649
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,660
My mom won't let me keep it.

650
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:04,380
She says playing with it saps my will.

651
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,620
Are you afraid your studies will be delayed?

652
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:10,280
And to think I used to envy you.

653
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:13,520
Okay.

654
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:14,900
How about this?

655
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,000
I'll raise this turtle for you.

656
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:18,560
Really?

657
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:19,690
Pinky swear.

658
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,200
Pinky swear.

659
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,360
Stamp.

660
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:26,200
Have you named this turtle?

661
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:27,660
His name is Xiaoba.

662
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:28,680
Lao Qi.

663
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,280
I'll raise Xiaoba for you,

664
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:31,680
as my apology to you.

665
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,440
Then we're good now.

666
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:35,960
By the way.

667
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:37,960
Let's join the rocket competition together.

668
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,160
Rocket competition?

669
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,000
Launch.

670
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:58,180
Launch successful! Launch successful!

671
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:01,760
Let's go. We're heading to Mars now.

672
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:02,360
Let's go!

673
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,080
Give me the oxygen mask.

674
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,520
Give it to me. Give it to me.

675
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:08,520
Mom!

676
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:09,540
Hello, Auntie.

677
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:11,000
Let's go to Earth.

678
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,120
Let me see.

679
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,690
You forgot the order again.

680
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:52,920
Wu Wei.

681
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,760
This part is very important.

682
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:56,420
Don't forget it in the finals.

683
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:57,200
Got it.

684
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,000
New max altitude record!

685
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:03,680
We won!

686
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:04,520
Team 3 of the Junior Group.

687
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,850
Won! First place in the qualifiers so far!

688
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:19,040
Mom.

689
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:21,450
I'm going to win the championship for you.

690
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:23,840
It's too late.

691
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:24,720
I'm leaving, Mom.

692
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:25,680
Slow down.

693
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,440
Don't be in such a rush.

694
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:37,520
My mom took me to the Math Olympiad.

695
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:39,760
But I'll definitely be back before the competition this afternoon.

696
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:40,890
You must wait for me.

697
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,960
Is Group 1 ready?

698
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:48,720
Get ready.

699
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:50,800
Is Group 2 ready?

700
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:51,600
Yes.

701
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:52,840
Don't miss any parts.

702
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:54,040
Get ready.

703
00:29:57,080 --> 00:29:57,680
Students,

704
00:29:58,360 --> 00:29:59,560
we're about to start.

705
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:00,600
Sir,

706
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:03,060
I have another teammate who hasn't arrived.

707
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,280
If you don't start assembling now, it will be too late.

708
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:07,880
Keep an eye on the time.

709
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,440
Mom,

710
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:14,040
I got second place this time.

711
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,120
Mom.

712
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:16,320
Mom.

713
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:18,380
I got second place.

714
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:20,360
Xiaoqi,

715
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,280
second place is useless.

716
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:24,400
Everything is meaningless if you don't win the championship.

717
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,460
Do you understand?

718
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:31,640
Mom, wait.

719
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:35,160
I promised Wu Wei a rocket race.

720
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:36,600
It's starting soon.

721
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,000
I have to go now.

722
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,600
Now I know why you only got second place.

723
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:44,760
All you think about is playing.

724
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,620
How can you win the championship?

725
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:54,660
Participating teams, get ready at the launch area.

726
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:07,720
Wu Wei.

727
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:11,840
Why are you so late?

728
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,600
You chickened out.

729
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,760
We agreed to join the competition and win together.

730
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,040
Why are you so late?

731
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,480
Is winning the championship that important?

732
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:24,610
Only the championship is meaningful.

733
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:27,640
Is the championship more important than your friend?

734
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:28,880
The championship is.

735
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:16,120
Weiwei,

736
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:19,800
pack,

737
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:21,800
pack your things.

738
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:24,600
Go to the hospital to see your mom.

739
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,320
Mom, Weiwei.

740
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:27,560
Mom.

741
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,400
Weiwei, Mom.

742
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,080
Weiwei, Weiwei, let me go.

743
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,120
Weiwei, don't be like this.

744
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,240
I want my mom.

745
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:33,760
Weiwei, let me go.

746
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:43,320
Mom only hopes you can become

747
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:45,960
the person you want to be.

748
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:48,360
When you grow up,

749
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,920
do what you like to do.

750
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:54,360
I hope you are happy every single day.

751
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,880
Dad is back.

752
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:14,600
Where are you going this early?

753
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:15,600
For an interview.

754
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:17,680
You've been to so many interviews,

755
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,120
but I've never seen you so neat.

756
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:20,200
When you have time,

757
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:23,000
can you polish my shoes for me?

758
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:24,240
Dad, it's different.

759
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,920
I'm going to the Space City today,

760
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,040
for an interview at the Flight Control Center.

761
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,400
You step on the gas pedal,

762
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:31,280
and under your feet is asphalt.

763
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:33,200
I'm navigating the space.

764
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:34,520
My next step is towards

765
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:36,640
the sea of stars.

766
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:40,040
What's the big deal about space?

767
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:42,280
Don't look down on my gas pedal.

768
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:18,280
Morning, Sister Jia.

769
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:19,520
Morning.

770
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:22,960
Sorry.

771
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:23,600
Excuse me, sorry.

772
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:24,360
No, sorry.

773
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:32,199
Sorry.

774
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:34,000
Please hold this for me, thanks.

775
00:34:34,159 --> 00:34:35,620
It's quite slippery here.

776
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:40,050
Are you here for the interview too?

777
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,320
It's just an interview.

778
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,449
Don't be so nervous.

779
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:45,840
Thanks.

780
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:48,080
It's starting soon. Hurry!

781
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:48,840
Front left.

782
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:52,920
Hello.

783
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,360
Is this the interview waiting area?

784
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:55,000
Yes.

785
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,159
You are also here for the interview?

786
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:56,760
Yes.

787
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,140
I remember you.

788
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,560
Robotics Competition, Storm Doghead.

789
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:23,080
I watched your match.

790
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:25,200
It was a pity you lost, though.

791
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,760
No, let me correct you.

792
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:28,080
We didn't lose.

793
00:35:28,080 --> 00:35:29,560
They cheated to win.

794
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,200
Our Aeronautics University was going for a three-peat.

795
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:32,360
Right.

796
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:34,160
Since it's fate that brought us here,

797
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:35,240
you should let me play with

798
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,900
your Storm Doghead sometime.

799
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:37,880
Rounding it up,

800
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:40,360
we can be considered brothers who shared a trench.

801
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,200
No problem.

802
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:42,600
Cai Bo'ao.

803
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:43,860
You can call me Caibao.

804
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:46,330
Wu Wei, from Aeronautics University.

805
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,880
You look younger than me.

806
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:50,480
Have you graduated with your master's degree?

807
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:51,240
No.

808
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,570
I have a Ph.D.

809
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:56,240
I got into the Junior Class at the University of Science and Technology at 14.

810
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,160
But compared to my classmates

811
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,400
who were 12 or 13,

812
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:00,920
I was a bit more mature.

813
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:02,320
Yeah.

814
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:06,480
What's this thick stack?

815
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:07,720
This?

816
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:10,360
It's a list of my published papers.

817
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,680
There are too many to carry,

818
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,210
so I just printed a catalog.

819
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:16,280
A catalog list?

820
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,440
A list.

821
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,560
What do you need the list for?

822
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:24,320
Wu Wei.

823
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:26,480
Thanks.

824
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:27,140
No worries.

825
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:28,280
Good luck.

826
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:28,800
Okay.

827
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:52,960
You may begin.

828
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:53,960
Hello, interviewers.

829
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:54,890
My name is Wu Wei.

830
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:55,960
I graduated from Aeronautics University,

831
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:58,320
majoring in Navigation, Guidance and Control at the School of Astronautics.

832
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,800
We've read your resume.

833
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:02,440
We want to know why you want to join Flight Control.

834
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,960
Influenced by my mom since childhood,

835
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,890
I wanted to be a Chinese astronaut.

836
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:06,880
But in high school,

837
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:07,840
because I failed the physical test,

838
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:09,320
I couldn't become one.

839
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:11,360
But I think even if I can't go to space,

840
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:13,560
being a star-herder is also quite cool.

841
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:16,960
You just said you were influenced by your mother.

842
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:17,440
Yes.

843
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:19,200
Does she like aerospace?

844
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,880
My mom is an aerospace worker.

845
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,240
She was in charge of logistics.

846
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,160
When I learned to read,

847
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:25,760
it all started with her aerospace magazines.

848
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,800
Then tell us your understanding of flight control.

849
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,680
I love aerospace and flight control.

850
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:33,880
In the vast space,

851
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,960
there are no road signs, nor are there directions.

852
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:38,120
If spacecraft are kites,

853
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:39,680
then we are the kite flyers.

854
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,160
Your grades are quite unbalanced.

855
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:42,400
A few subjects are okay,

856
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:44,280
but the others barely passed.

857
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:46,120
My major subject grades are very good.

858
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:47,480
Because I put all my time and energy

859
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:48,960
into my major subjects.

860
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,480
